    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Draft social posts with Notion and WordPress at scale\n\n**Pattern:** Content Generation · **Level:** Advanced · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nDraft social posts with Notion and WordPress at scale. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual listening is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nHourly Schedule → Read Recent from Notion → Newest First → Trim to Digest Size → Summarize Content (AI) → Render as HTML → Post Digest to Slack → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to content generation without manual effort\n- Anyone automating listening in marketing\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Improves response time\n- Standardizes the process every time\n- Responds in seconds\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Anthropic API key; Notion integration token; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "f26eee10-3ea2-8a58-e65e-e027dc451b55",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
